Tutorial

Darkwind starts a short tutorial for new characters. It teaches the basics
without locking you into a separate training area.

Commands:
  tutorial          Show your current tutorial step.
  tutorial status   Show whether the tutorial is active, skipped, or finished.
  tutorial hint     Repeat a concrete command suggestion.
  tutorial skip     Stop the tutorial for this character.
  tutorial restart  Start over if you skipped or did not finish.
  engage nim        Talk with Nim and unlock the next lesson.

The tutorial covers looking, examining, movement, inventory, the newbie
channel, getting starter equipment from Erga, wearing and wielding gear,
traveling to the newbie farm, basic combat safety, newbie combat commands,
score, and accepting a first newbie quest.

Nim follows you as a small NPC while the tutorial is active. Each lesson starts
by engaging her. Use engage nim, choose that you understand the lesson, then run
the command or action she gives you. When you complete it, Nim will ask you to
engage her again for the next lesson.

Nim knows the way. During travel lessons she computes directions from
wherever you are actually standing: tutorial hint always includes the
current route, the engage menu offers "Which way do I go?", and if you walk
the wrong way for a couple of rooms she calls out a correction. If you end
up somewhere she cannot chart, ncot returns you to the Center of Town and
she will re-plot from there.

Each lesson also names a help topic to read for the bigger picture, and the
journey continues after the tutorial in help guide.

Erga's Newbie Shop gives level 1-5 characters free starter gear with the
equipment command. The tutorial shows how to wear the leather and shield,
wield the dagger, find the newbie farm, and practice kill, wimpy, mon, nheal,
nkick, npunch, and ncot.
